Enum WordParser.WordType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<WordParser.WordType>
org.eclipse.persistence.jpa.jpql.WordParser.WordType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<WordParser.WordType>, java.lang.constant.Constable
Enclosing class:
WordParser
public static enum WordParser.WordType extends Enum<WordParser.WordType>
This enumeration determines the type of word that was scanned. It will be set by WordParser.word(), WordParser.wordEndPosition(), WordParser.wordEndPosition(int).

  • Enum Constant Summary

    Enum Constants
    Enum Constant
    Description
    INPUT_PARAMETER
    The word being scanned is an input parameter, it starts with either ':' or '?'.
    NUMERIC_LITERAL
    The word being scanned is a numeric literal (decimal or hexadecimal number).
    STRING_LITERAL
    The word being scanned is a string literal, it starts with either ''' or '"'.
    UNDEFINED
    No word was scanned, this is usually set when the cursor is at the end of the text.
    WORD
    The word being scanned anything else other than an input parameter, numeric literal or string literal.
